article.headline: Lehigh 63, Army 45
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Nick Monserez scored 20 points and Jose Olivero chipped in 19 points and nine rebounds as Lehigh beat Army 63-45 on Friday night. Lehigh (10-9, 4-2 Patriot League) opened the game with a 23-6 run, helped by a pair of 3-pointers by Monserez, who scored eight points in the first 10 minutes. Army (3-15, 1-5) closed the half on a 14-2 run to cut Lehigh's lead to seven, but Lehigh held the Black Knights to just 7-of-24 shooting in the second half. For the game, the Mountain Hawks shot 41 percent from the field while holding Army to 35 percent. Lehigh, which had lost two straight, dominated the glass, out-rebounding Army 39-20. Colin Harris led Army with 18 points, while Matt Bell scored 13.
